org.jetel.data

Class DataRecordWithInvalidState

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jetel.data.DataRecord
      • org.jetel.data.DataRecordImpl
        • org.jetel.data.DataRecordWithInvalidState
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<java.lang.Object>, java.lang.Iterable<DataField>

    public class DataRecordWithInvalidState
extends DataRecordImpl
    Implementation of DataRecord interface, which use DataFieldWithInvalidState instead of regular DataFieldImpl. This type of record is able to mark a field with validity flag. Access to an invalid value in a field throw DataFieldInvalidStateException.
